Author-Name:    Simpson, R David
Author-Name:  Sedjo, Roger A
Author-Name:  Reid, John W
Title:   Valuing Biodiversity for Use in Pharmaceutical Research. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 163-85
Issue: 1
Volume: 104
Year: 1996
Month:  February 
Abstract:
  'Biodiversity prospecting' has been touted as a mechanism for both
 discovering new pharmaceutical products and saving endangered ecosystems.
 It is unclear what values may arise from such activities, however.
 Evidence from transactions is incomplete and existing theoretical models
 are flawed. The authors calculate an upper bound on the value of the
 'marginal species.' Even under favorable assumptions this bound is modest.
 Slightly modified assumptions lead to drastically lower estimates. The
 authors extend their findings to the value of the marginal hectare of
 habitat and find that the incentives for habitat conservation generated by
 private pharmaceutical research are also, at best, very modest.  Copyright 1996 by University of Chicago Press.
