Author-Name:    Telser, Lester G
Title:   Competition and the Core. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 85-107
Issue: 1
Volume: 104
Year: 1996
Month:  February 
Abstract:
  Core theory is a powerful tool to find competitive market-clearing
 prices. A familiar economic setting shows this, beginning with a single
 commodity produced using many factors of production and ending with the
 general case of many outputs and inputs. The analysis describes when the
 market has a core. When it has no core, there is a least upper bound on
 the payment each firm that does not participate in a central market must
 make that serves as an inducement to restore the core. Each firm can avoid
 this penalty by trading in the central market, resulting in
 market-clearing prices.  Copyright 1996 by University of Chicago Press.
